Update is coming tonight. You will have the option to play with or without Scatterer.

Wait, since I have an untrained eye, Which one do you prefer? Just looking at these pictures, I am leaning towards "Without Scatterer".

13 minutes ago, JedTech said:

Wait, since I have an untrained eye, Which one do you prefer? Just looking at these pictures, I am leaning towards "Without Scatterer".

Both look good, but at the moment there are some bugs with scatterer in 1.4 that make it hard to use. So for this update, until Scatterer has its fixes in place, I recommend going without Scatterer

UPDATE

Change Log

v1.3.0

  • Update for KSP 1.4.1
  • Implemented EVE atmospheres
    • While not as pretty as Scatterer, it greatly improves performance.
  • Once Scatterer updates and fixes some bugs it will still be recommended. In its current state, I recommend not using it.
  • REQUIRES SVE_Textures v1.0.5

EVE atmospheres are back ! Finally !?

You rock Galileo !

2 hours ago, Dafni said:

which one is it now? did the recommendation change for some reason between these posts?

No nothing has changed. I wouldn’t use scatterer right now. When Blackrack implements some fixes, I will go back to recommending it.

Just now, Athlonic said:

Wait what !?!

EVE atmospheres are back ! Finally !?

You rock Galileo ! 

Not exactly, I use a cloud layer to gain the effect. Currently there is a small transition that happens around 25km as you fly through the layer and it clips the camera. I have approached the EVE dev with a potential solution and hopefully it can happen sooner than later. But I hope it is able to fill the need for now.
